Program: Outlook
Title: I Didn't Know Who or Where I Was
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p020tdpy
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 20 Jun 2014
American writer, David Stuart MacLean, became psychotic after a bad reaction to an anti-malarial drug. Even now, 10 years on, his mind is not back to how it was before. He has written a book about losing his memory, called The Answer to the Riddle is Me. The Spanish tenor, Placido Domingo, talks about preparing to sing at the football World Cup in Brazil. Shorah Qadiry came top in Afghanistan's national university entrance exam, the Kankor. She tells us of her plans to help rebuild her country and her ambitions to become a doctor. (Photo: David Stuart MacLean. Credit: Heather Eidson) Show less